
<h2 class='bd-b-solid-shade2 mb-100 fw-light'>Padding and Margin</h2>

<p>Padding and margin use <code>em</code>. Relative to the font-size of the element 
(2em means 2 times the size of the current font).</p>

<p>pa, means padding all. px, means padding-top and padding-bottom. py means padding-left and padding-right. And it goes for eachs l,r,t,b </p>

{% set sizes= [25,50,75,100,200,300,400,500,600,700] %}
{% set sides= ['a','x','y','t','r','l','b'] %}

<div class='label'>Head to head</div>

<div class='debug'>
	<div class='px-300'><span>px-300</span></div>
	<div class='mx-300'><span>mx-300</span></div>
</div>

<div class='label'>Catalog</div>

<div class='debug'>
	{% for w in sides %}
		{% for s in sizes %}
			<div class='p{{w}}-{{s}}'><span>p{{w}}-{{s}}</span></div>
		{% endfor %}
	{% endfor %}
</div>


<div class='debug'>
	{% for w in sides %}
		{% for s in sizes %}
			<div class='m{{w}}-{{s}}'><span>m{{w}}-{{s}}</span></div>
		{% endfor %}
	{% endfor %}
</div>

